answers.body_markdown:
Instead of capturing all the three `,` into a single capturing group you can capture them as three separate groups and add the value in desired format before or after the particular group

    ([^,]+),([^,]+),([^,]+)(?:,|$)

[![enter image description here][1]][1]

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    let str = `18 S, 95,food,19 S, 48,food,19 S,3 400,auto repair`

    let final = str.replace(/([^,]+),([^,]+),([^,]+)(?:,|$)/g, &#39;$1 - $2 $ - $3\n&#39;)

    console.log(final)

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/QwXIG.png
